### Session & Header Dimension Config

Add to `opentelemetry.metrics.api_metrics` in `tyk.conf`:

```json
[
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.apikey",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per API key (last 6 chars)",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "session",
        "key": "api_key",
        "label": "api_key_suffix"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.oauth",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per OAuth client",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "session",
        "key": "oauth_id",
        "label": "oauth_client_id"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "response_code",
        "label": "response_code"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.portal",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per portal app/org",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "session",
        "key": "portal_app",
        "label": "portal_app"
      },
      {
        "source": "session",
        "key": "portal_org",
        "label": "portal_org"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.tenant",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per tenant (from X-Tenant-ID header)",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "header",
        "key": "X-Tenant-ID",
        "label": "tenant_id",
        "default": "unknown"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "response_code",
        "label": "response_code"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.latency.by.tenant",
    "type": "histogram",
    "histogram_source": "total",
    "description": "End-to-end latency per tenant",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "header",
        "key": "X-Tenant-ID",
        "label": "tenant_id",
        "default": "unknown"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

### Response Header Dimension Config

Add to `opentelemetry.metrics.api_metrics` in `tyk.conf`:

> ⚠️ `response_header` dimensions are **only populated on the success path**. Error responses (upstream failures, bad destinations) will use the configured `default` value.

```json
[
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.with.cache",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests tracked by cache status (from X-Cache-Status response header)",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "response_header",
        "key": "X-Cache-Status",
        "label": "cache_status",
        "default": "MISS"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.backend.version",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per backend version (from X-Server-Version response header)",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "response_header",
        "key": "X-Server-Version",
        "label": "backend_version",
        "default": "unknown"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.content.type",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests tracked by response Content-Type",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "response_header",
        "key": "Content-Type",
        "label": "content_type",
        "default": "unknown"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

**Use case examples:**
- Cache hit rate monitoring: backend sets `X-Cache-Status: HIT` or `MISS`
- Canary deploys: backend sets `X-Server-Version: v2.1.0` — track traffic shift from v1→v2
- Content negotiation: detect when APIs unexpectedly return `text/html` instead of `application/json`

### Context Variable & Metadata Dimension Config

Add to `opentelemetry.metrics.api_metrics` in `tyk.conf`:

> Context variables (`source: "context"`) are set by Tyk middleware. Use a **Go Plugin** or **Virtual Endpoint** to extract values from JWT claims, session data, or request attributes and store them as context variables.

```json
[
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.tier",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per subscription tier (context variable)",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "context",
        "key": "tier",
        "label": "subscription_tier",
        "default": "standard"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "response_code",
        "label": "response_code"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.latency.by.tier",
    "type": "histogram",
    "histogram_source": "total",
    "description": "End-to-end latency per subscription tier",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "context",
        "key": "tier",
        "label": "subscription_tier",
        "default": "standard"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.region",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per geographic region",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "context",
        "key": "region",
        "label": "region",
        "default": "unknown"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.route",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per API route path",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "route",
        "label": "route"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_name",
        "label": "api_name"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "method",
        "label": "method"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "response_code",
        "label": "response_code"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "scheme",
        "label": "scheme"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.org",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per organization",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "org_id",
        "label": "org_id"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_name",
        "label": "api_name"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "method",
        "label": "method"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by.version",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Requests per API version",
    "dimensions": [
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_version",
        "label": "api_version"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "api_id",
        "label": "api_id"
      },
      {
        "source": "metadata",
        "key": "response_code",
        "label": "response_code"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```
